readme.md

Awesome

Awesome Gideros

   A curated list of awesome resources for the
   [http://giderosmobile.com/]Gideros Game Development Framework that
   allows you to easily create games and apps for Android, iOS, HTML5,
   WinRT and Desktop (Windows, OSX). Please feel free to contribute to the
   list by making a pull request.

Contents

     * Getting Started
     * Resources
          + Tutorials and Tips
          + Full game examples
          + Publications
          + IDEs and Editors
          + Graphics and Shaders
          + Scene Managment
          + Input
          + Animation and Tweens
          + Tilemaps
          + Camera
          + Audio
          + Saving and Loading
          + Monetization
          + GUI
          + 3D
          + Plugins
     * Useful Lua-Libraries
     * License and Contriuting

Getting Started

     * [http://giderosmobile.com/download]Download Gideros - Get Gideros
       here (it is free but donations are welcome!).
     * [http://docs.giderosmobile.com/]Getting Started Manual - Check here
       first to get an overview of the framework.
     * [http://docs.giderosmobile.com/reference/]API Reference - Whenever
       you need to figure something out- this is the first place to go.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/]Forum - Join the very helpful
       community.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/code/]Online Editor - Try Gideros in your
       browser without installing anything.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/examples]Online Examples - See some of
       the capabilites of Gideros in your browser.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/guide]Developer Guide - Official list of
       guides and tutorials.

Resources

   A collection of resources (blog and forum entries, websites, packages
   etc) for Gideros

Tutorials and Tips

     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IRLxBijIX50]Introductory Video
       Tutorial - By one of the maintainers of Gideros.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6894/publishing-tutorial
       #Item_7]Publishing to Android - Getting started with publishing to
       Android.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/4892/software-improve-wh
       at-kind-of-skills-do-you-need]Improving performance - Forum thread
       with hints about improving the performance of Gideros apps.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5870/new-desktop-api-tes
       t/p1]Desktop API - Overview of the Desktop API to manipulate mouse
       cursor and window decorations.

Full game examples

     * [http://bluebilby.com/2013/05/08/gideros-mobile-tutorial-creating-y
       our-first-game/]Simple square-dodge game - Introductory tutorial
       about creating a simple square-dodge game.
     * [https://programmingbymoonlight.com/roguelike-intro/]Top-down
       roguelike Tutorial - Extensive tutorial series about making a
       turn-based roguelike in Gideros.
     * [http://blog.hotbutteredgames.com/post/143878823915/gideros-tutoria
       l-a-simple-box2d-game-gideros-is-a]Breakout Clone - Tutorial about
       creating a Breakout-like game using Gideros and Box2D.
     * [http://www.moosader.com/learn/introduction-to-mobile-game-developm
       ent/]"Grab the treasure" course - Comprehensive getting-started
       guide to Gideros by developing a small game.

Publications

   Books about Gideros
     * [https://www.packtpub.com/game-development/gideros-mobile-game-deve
       lopment]Gideros Mobile Game Development - Comprehensive book about
       developing a game for mobile with Gideros.
     * [http://www.apress.com/us/book/9781430246626]Learn Lua for iOS Game
       Development - Introducing a variety of Lua-based game development
       frameworks including Gideros.

IDEs and Editors

   Code editors and plugins that work with Gideros
     * [http://www.indiedb.com/tutorials/gideros-with-zerobrane]Using
       ZeroBrane Studio with Gideros - Introductory tutorial for using ZBS
       with Gideros Remote Preview.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wPYvJxFxMkM]Live Coding with
       Gideros and ZeroBrane Studio - Video showing the live coding
       capabilities of ZBS and Gideros.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GIipyzSpSr0]ZeroBrane Studio
       integration and debugging - Video tutorial by the creator of ZBS.
     * [https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=devCAT.lua-deb
       ug]Visual Studio Code plugin - With Gideros support (Windows only).
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5218/gideros-sublime-tex
       t-3-package-for-osx-windows-version-0-10/p1]Sublime Text 3 plugin -
       Adding Gideros support to ST3.

Graphics and Shaders

     * [http://bit.ly/2pkF09m]Shaders in Gideros - Introductory text about
       shaders in Gideros.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6667/shadertoy-viewer-be
       ta-shaders-from-www-shadertoy-com-in-gideros/p1]Shadertoy viewer -
       Check out shaders from Shadertoy using Gideros.
     * [http://www.indiedb.com/engines/gideros/tutorials/clipping-in-gider
       os-with-rendertarget]Intro to clipping and the RenderTarget -
       Text-based tutorial on how to use the RenderTarget class to create
       a clipping effect.

Scene Management

     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Manage-Scenes-in-Gideros-M
       obile]SceneManager - Easily switch between scenes with or without
       transitions.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/1474/passing-variables-w
       ith-scene-manager/p1]Passing variables using the SceneManager -
       Passing variables to the next scene when using the scene manager.

Input

     * [https://github.com/stetso/GidSwipe]GidSwipe - Easy to use tap and
       swipe manager for mobile.
     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Detecting-Gestures-in-Gide
       ros]Gestures - Define and detect complex gestures from points a
       list of points.
     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Using-Accelerometer-with-B
       ox2d-in-Gideros]Accelerometer - Quick example of how to use the
       device accelerometer as input.
     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Gideros-Shake-detection]Sh
       ake detection - Small snippet to detect device shake.

Animation and Tweens

     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Gideros-GTween-with-easing
       ]GTween - Tween sprite variables with this library (comes with all
       the easing functions you need).
     * [http://bluebilby.com/2013/05/12/gideros-mobile-tutorial-animated-m
       ovieclips/]Animation using MovieClip - Tutorial on how to animate
       sprites using the MovieClip class.
     * [https://github.com/nascode/gideros_animsheet]Spriteheet animation
       class - Class that helps with creating and playing animations from
       spritesheets.

Tilemaps

     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6353/collision-with-any-
       object/p1]Collision with Tilemaps - Examples and suggestions on how
       to make stuff collide with the tiles in your tilemap.

Camera

     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/2715/camera-class-with-k
       inetics-and-pinch-to-zoom/p1]Smooth camera with Drag and
       Pinch-to-Zoom - Useful class implementation for a camera in a
       mobile game.

Audio

     * [http://bluebilby.com/2013/04/18/gideros-mobile-tutorial-playing-mu
       sic-and-sound-effects/]Intro to using audio with Gideros - Tutorial
       about generating and using sounds with Gideros.

Saving and Loading

     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6918/saving-and-loading-
       data-files#Item_1]Using JSON - Loading and saving manually via
       JSON.
     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Save-and-load-data-module-
       for-Gideros-Mobile]DataSaver module - User-friendly wrapper to make
       saving and loading data as easy as possible.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5625/simple-savegame-enc
       ryption/p1]Encrypting save files - Some ideas (with code) about
       securing the save files from unwanted manipulation.

Monetization

     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5801/tuto-video-tutorial
       -how-to-add-admob-plugin-to-your-app]Admob integration - Video
       tutorial about integrating Admob into your game.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/5806/tuto-video-tutorial
       -how-to-add-google-services-to-your-app]Google Service integration
       - Second part of the Admob tutorial showing Google Play Service
       integration.

GUI

     * [https://github.com/Nlcke/layout]Layout - Comprehensive Gideors GUI
       framework
       ([http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/6651/layout-gideros-gui
       -framework#Item_23]forum entry).
     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Gideros-mobile-button-clas
       s]Button class - Simple class for creating clickable buttons.
     * [http://appcodingeasy.com/Gideros-Mobile/Easy-input-for-choosing-pa
       ckages-or-levels-in-Gideros-Mobile]AceSlide class - Sliding
       UI-Element that can be used for example for level selection.

3D

   Note: 3D support is still in development but if you like to play around
   with it already, here are some starting points
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IfHwdJD6ad8]Tutorial using 3D in
       Gideros - Introduction by one of the maintainers of Gideros.

Plugins

     * [https://github.com/mertkurum/GiderosStoreReview]SKStoreReview -
       Gideros Plugin for SKStoreReviewController iOS 10.3+.
     * [http://giderosmobile.com/forum/discussion/1025/step-by-step-how-to
       -write-a-c-plugin-and-deploy-it-to-the-desktop-windows-player]C++
       plugin development - Getting started with Gideros plugin
       development in C++.

Useful Lua-Libraries

   General Lua libraries that are useful in gamedev but are not Gideros
   specific
     * [https://github.com/rxi/lume]lume - Great collection of functions
       that are useful for game development.
     * [https://github.com/kikito/inspect.lua]inspect - Easily
       pretty-print your tables to the console in a readable way.
     * [http://yonaba.github.io/Jumper/]jumper - Super-fast grid-based
       pathfinding for Lua.
     * [https://github.com/kikito/bump.lua]bump - Simple, flexible and
       fast library for collision detection using axis-aligned bounding
       boxes.
     * [https://github.com/rm-code/Bresenham]Bresenham - Bresenham's line
       algorithm, implemented in Lua.

Related Awesome Lists

     * [https://github.com/LewisJEllis/awesome-lua]awesome-lua
     * [https://github.com/love2d-community/awesome-love2d]awesome-love2d
     * [https://github.com/mbrukman/awesome-gamedev]awesome-gamedev

